### 1. Create a photography package
POST http://localhost:4000/api/packages
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Wedding Premium",
    "price": 1500,
    "duration": "8 hours",
    "services": "Photography, Drone, Album"
}

### 2. Get all photography packages (Returns DB records or fallback arrays)
GET http://localhost:4000/api/packages

### 3. Get all photographers for the Booking Dropdown
GET http://localhost:4000/api/photographers

### 4. Check photographer availability for a specific date
GET http://localhost:4000/api/photographers/availability?date=2026-06-15

### 5. Create a booking 
POST http://localhost:4000/api/bookings
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "customer_name": "John Doe",
    "package_id": 1,
    "photographer_id": 1,
    "date": "2026-06-15",
    "event_type": "Wedding"
}

### 6. Try to create an OVERLAPPING booking (Should return a 400 status error)
POST http://localhost:4000/api/bookings
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "customer_name": "Alice Smith",
    "package_id": 1,
    "photographer_id": 1,
    "date": "2026-06-15",
    "event_type": "Pre-Wedding"
}

### 7. List bookings with filters and pagination applied
GET http://localhost:4000/api/bookings?status=Pending&limit=5&offset=0

### 8. Update booking status
PUT http://localhost:4000/api/bookings/1/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "status": "Confirmed"
}

### 9. Get complete studio metrics dashboard statistics
GET http://localhost:4000/api/dashboard/studio

### 10. Get gallery preview items (Includes automatic DB hang safety threshold)
GET http://localhost:4000/api/gallery

### 11. Get revenue analytics dataset for visual charts
GET http://localhost:4000/api/analytics/revenue

### 12. Get booking validation reminder alerts
GET http://localhost:4000/api/bookings/reminders